Sure! Here's a simple JavaScript function that sorts an array of strings alphabetically:

```javascript
function sortStrings Alphabetically(arr) {
  return arr.sort();
}

// Example usage:
const strings = ["banana", "apple", "cherry", "date"];
const sortedStrings = sortStringsAlphabetically(strings);
console.log(sortedStrings); // Output: ["apple", "banana", "cherry", "date"]
```

This function uses the `sort` method of arrays in JavaScript, which by default sorts the elements in alphabetical order. Just pass your array of strings to this function, and it will return a new array with the strings sorted alphabetically.
